    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-11-27T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-11-27T17:00:00-05:00" n="568"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d568">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 103.97/58a</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Food Administrator</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_HHC1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hoover</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the Food Administration Representative at
                        London</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SLP1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Sheldon</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="1" xml:id="d568fn1">Transmitted by the Secretary of State
                        through the Ambassador in Great Britain (No. 5914).</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-11-27T17:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 27, 1917, 5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>For <persName corresp="#p_RLD1">Lord Rhondda</persName>: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>It appears to me that the only solution of wheat situation lies in the
                            implementing Australian, Indian and Argentine supplies and insistence on
                            the part of all food controllers of the imperative necessity of the
                            priority provision of shipping for this purpose. We are using every
                            effort to reduce consumption but do not see at present any larger supply
                            than amount mentioned unless provision is made for replacement from
                            Argentine at later date.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_HHC1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Hoover</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
